That latter provision, which is supplemented by the Protocol (No. 26) on Services of General Interest (
OJ 2010 C 83, p. 308
) and, as regards the field at issue in the present case, by the Protocol (No. 29) on the System of Public Broadcasting in the Member States (
OJ 2010 C 83, p. 312
), cannot be interpreted in isolation having regard merely to its wording without also taking into account the additional information in those protocols.
